Changed traffic conditions for night works will be in place from Sunday 18 August to Thursday 22 August.

There will be a lane closures and a speed reduction to 40km/h during the work areas on Maitland Road to allow asphalting to proceed. Subject to weather, the traffic arrangements will be:

  • Sunday 18 August, there will be no right turn from Maitland Road into the Newcastle Inner City Bypass or Old Maitland Road at Sandgate. A detour will be in place via Wallsend Road 800 metres towards Newcastle. The detour will not impact outbound traffic travelling from Newcastle on Maitland Road. 
  • From Monday 19 August to Wednesday 21 August there will be no right turn from Maitland Road into the Newcastle Inner City Bypass. There will be a contraflow for inbound and outbound traffic on Maitland Road between Ironbark Creek bridge to the Newcastle Inner City Bypass. A detour will be in place via Wallsend Road 800 metres towards Newcastle. The detour will not impact outbound traffic travelling from Newcastle on Maitland Road. 
  • Thursday 22 August, there will be a contra flow for both inbound and outbound lanes on Maitland Road to the north of Ironbark Creek with one lane operating in either direction. 

Over Size Over Mass operators and/or vehicles operating under permit with a ground contact wider than 3.2m and/or overall width greater than 4.5m are advised to contact the project team at least one day ahead of movement on 1800 515 141. Significant delays will occur if no contact is made. Please note vehicles travelling under a Permit must not travel off the approved route listed in the permit unless an updated permit is obtained from the NHVR.

A temporary speed of 60km/h will remain in place through the project work zone during ongoing day work, and a reduction to 40km/h during night work.
